The programme includes the following topics: set theory, natural numbers, mathematical word problems, geometric shapes, teaching math at pre-school.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give students necessary knowledge and skills in the main questions of arithmetics, basics of set theory  and geometric shapes to teach math at pre-school and on school stage one.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course a student will 1) know the properties of the set of natural numbers, 2) understand the concept of sets, 3) be able to formulate and solve mathematical word problems and justify solutions through critical evaluation and analysis; 4) know and group geometric shapes; 5) know the content and principles of teaching pre-school math .
